headlines.description: Khalil Small sank four free throws in the last 51 seconds, giving Green Bay just enough of a lead to survive a last-second 3-pointer and hang on to defeat Oakland 80-79 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Small comes up big in Green Bay's 80-79  win over Oakland

headlines.description: E.C. Matthews scored 18 points with five rebounds and Rhode Island cruised to an 83-64 win over George Mason on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Rhode Island cruises to 83-64 win over George Mason

headlines.description: Yuta Watanabe scored 18 points and Arnaldo Toro grabbed 12 rebounds and scored 10 points and George Washington held off Saint Joseph's 70-64 on Saturday in an Atlantic 10 opener.
headlines.shortLinkText: George Washington beats Saint Joseph's in A-10 opener, 70-64

headlines.description: Kyle Williams had 16 of his 21 points in the final 6  1/2 minutes on Saturday night and Norfolk State rallied from a 10-point deficit to beat Stony Brook 74-68.
headlines.shortLinkText: Williams rallies Norfolk State over Stony Brook 74-68

headlines.description: Drew McDonald had 19 points and 12 rebounds -- his fourth consecutive double-double -- to help Northern Kentucky beat Illinois-Chicago 86-51 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: McDonald leads Northern Kentucky past Illinois-Chicago 86-51

headlines.description: Nick Dixon scored nine of his 21 points in the final 10 minutes to help UT Rio Grande Valley rally past Hampton 80-69 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: UT Rio Grande Valley rallies to beat Hampton 80-69

headlines.description: Kenneth Ogbe scored 23 points including a key 3-pointer and Utah Valley beat Cal State Fullerton 87-78 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Utah Valley makes 30 FTs, beats Cal State Fullerton 87-78

headlines.description: Souley Boum scored a career-high 26 points and San Francisco cruised to an 84-61 victory over Portland on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Boum scores 26 in San Francisco's 84-61 romp over Portland

nowFeed.headline: Oklahoma's Trae Young, on his recent offensive struggles: "I’m getting guarded like nobody else in the country is being guarded, scouted on like no one else in the country. It’s a mystery coming out each and every game to try and figure out how a team is going to guard me and how I’m going to dictate how my team wins. … It’s a lot tougher for me to score now than it was in the beginning. ... It’s a process. Right now, it’s tough."
